Hello,


I found a lot of kernel memory allocation calls without checking of the return value, in particular i tested the code under the folder 'sys'.

The bugs, and FP also, were found using coccinelle, maybe you should use it in your software life-cycle.


For example, take the function 'vchiq_platform_init_state()' at https://github.com/freebsd/freebsd-src/blob/0b4f2ab0e91307bd1fa6e884b0fccef9d10d5a2d/sys/contrib/vchiq/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_2835_arm.c#L233-L246

As we can see from the output below, it might cause a null pointer dereference. The output below was generated using coccinelle, which uses diff-like annotations.

```
diff -u -p a/contrib/vchiq/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_2835_arm.c b/contrib/vchiq/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_2835_arm.c
--- a/contrib/vchiq/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_2835_arm.c
+++ b/contrib/vchiq/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_2835_arm.c
@@ -236,6 +236,9 @@ vchiq_platform_init_state(VCHIQ_STATE_T
 {
    VCHIQ_STATUS_T status = VCHIQ_SUCCESS;
    state->platform_state = kzalloc(sizeof(VCHIQ_2835_ARM_STATE_T), GFP_KERNEL);
+   if (state->platform_state == NULL) {
+      return -ENOMEM;
+   }
    ((VCHIQ_2835_ARM_STATE_T*)state->platform_state)->inited = 1;
    status = vchiq_arm_init_state(state, &((VCHIQ_2835_ARM_STATE_T*)state->platform_state)->arm_state);
    if(status != VCHIQ_SUCCESS)

```

This behavior is already patched in linux, as shown here (vchiq_2835_arm.c merged into vchiq_arm.c):
https://github.com/torvalds/linux/blob/7203062171db6669f746d14148c4af76af619e74/drivers/staging/vc04_services/interface/vchiq_arm/vchiq_arm.c#L580-L594
